    {"collapsed": false, "gridPos": {"h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 41}, "id": 10, "panels": [],
     "title": "📖 No data yet? — set up the GPU exporter on .240", "type": "row"},
    {
      "datasource": {"type": "grafana", "uid": "-- Grafana --"},
      "description": "",
      "gridPos": {"h": 10, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 42}, "id": 11,
      "options": {"code": {"language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false},
                  "content": "### Quickest path — `nvidia_gpu_exporter` + Grafana Alloy\n\nOn `.240`:\n\n```bash\n# 1. Install the exporter (one binary, runs as systemd)\ncurl -sSL https://github.com/utkuozdemir/nvidia_gpu_exporter/releases/latest/download/nvidia_gpu_exporter_$(uname -m | sed s/x86_64/amd64/)_linux.tar.gz \\\n  | sudo tar -C /usr/local/bin -xzf - nvidia_gpu_exporter\n\nsudo tee /etc/systemd/system/nvidia_gpu_exporter.service <<'EOF'\n[Unit]\nDescription=NVIDIA GPU Prometheus Exporter\nAfter=network.target\n[Service]\nExecStart=/usr/local/bin/nvidia_gpu_exporter --web.listen-address=:9835\nRestart=always\n[Install]\nWantedBy=multi-user.target\nEOF\nsudo systemctl enable --now nvidia_gpu_exporter\n\n# Verify\ncurl -s localhost:9835/metrics | head -20\n```\n\n### Ship metrics to Grafana Cloud\n\nUse Alloy (if you already have it for other stuff on .240, just add this; if not, install via `https://github.com/grafana/alloy`):\n\n```alloy\nprometheus.scrape \"nvidia_gpu\" {\n  targets    = [{__address__ = \"localhost:9835\", instance = \"wags-ai-240\"}]\n  forward_to = [prometheus.remote_write.grafana_cloud.receiver]\n  job_name   = \"nvidia_gpu\"\n}\n```\n\nWithin 1 min the panels above will populate. If you'd rather use **DCGM Exporter** (NVIDIA's official, fancier), this dashboard supports both — the queries fall back from `nvidia_smi_*` to `DCGM_FI_DEV_*` automatically.\n",
                  "mode": "markdown"},
      "pluginVersion": "11.0.0",
      "title": "Recipe — installing the exporter on .240", "type": "text"
    }
